                  <persName id="t17970426-17-person185">
                  WILLIAM
                   LAYTON
               <interp inst="t17970426-17-person185" type="surname" value="LAYTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970426-17-person185" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17970426-17-person185" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am bailiff to Mr. Riedge who lives at Elstree; he lost a fat hog in the night of the 23d of February; I found the pig on Barnet-common.</p>
               <p>ANOTHER WITNESS sworn. - Mr. Layton came and told me Mr. Riedge had lost a hog; I got up directly, and we overtook the man on Barnetcommon; they had got him in a string; we secured the men and the hog.</p>
               <p>Q.(To Layton). How were they driving the hog? - A. I was not near enough to know whether they had him in a string or not.</p>
               <p>Q. Was the prisoner one of these men driving the hog? - A. I did not see him then, just before I got to him he was making his escape.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I had nothing to do with the hog, I was not near it.</p>
               <p>
